               <p>Witness for the Defence.</p>
               <p>MRS. RIGBY. I am landlady of the house; the prisoner was very much intoxicated from the Monday - he came home that Tuesday very drunk; he went up stairs for half an hour, then I saw him no more till he came home at night - he went to the prosecutor, and said he had taken a wrong shirt.</p>
